==English==
===Etymology===
From the Sanskrit ''[[sūtra]]'' (''precept''; lit. ''thread''). Entered into English 1801.
===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''sutra'''
#(''Hinduism'') Any of various [[aphoristic]] [[doctrinal]] [[summaries]] produced for [[memorization]]
#(''Buddhism'') A [[scriptural]] [[narrative]], especially a  [[discourse]] of the [[Buddha]]
